timelineitem.name: CREW DRAGON DOCKS WITH ISS
timelineitem.text: Crew Dragon docked with the International Space Station on March 3 at 3:02 a.m. PST, becoming the first American spacecraft to autonomously dock with the orbiting laboratory

timelineitem.name: FALCON HEAVY FIRST FLIGHT

timelineitem.name: FIRST DRAGON REFLIGHT
timelineitem.text: This Dragon resupply mission represented the first reflight of a commercial spacecraft to and from the International Space Station.
